ProcedureHelp.#cdata:
Syntax: PROC NESTED <options> ; 
    CLASS variables </ option> ; 
    VAR variables ; 
    BY variables ; 

The NESTED procedure performs random-effects analysis of variance for data from an 
experiment with a nested (hierarchical) structure. 

Note that PROC NESTED is appropriate for models with only classification effects; 
it does not handle models that contain continuous covariates. For random effects 
models with covariates, use either the GLM or MIXED procedure.
